Former partner at BAIN SA, Athol Williams will give evidence. JOHANNESBURG - The state capture inquiry will hear South African Revenue Services (SARS) related evidence on Tuesday. Former partner at BAIN SA, Athol Williams will give evidence. READ: Bain & Company's image takes another blow The Zondo Commission will also hear testimony from SARS employee, Vlok Symington. Later in the day, the commission is scheduled to have an evening session to hear the cross-examination of Minister Pravin Gordhan by former Sars Commissioner, Tom Moyane.